name: Blue Puni
library_note: Blue Puni is all around the world. Weak but vigorous and grows if left alone.

name: Green Puni
library_note: Green Puni is often found in grasslands and forests. It snaps if its sunbathing is disturbed, but its weak.

name: Red Puni
library_note: Red Puni lives in hot areas. As the temperature drops, it loses its energy.

name: Flower Puni
library_note: Despite its cute appearance, this Puni uses the flowers on its head to lure in prey.

name: Black Puni
library_note: Black Puni. They suddenly leap out of the darkness and feel a sense of fulfilment in surprising adventurers.

name: Silver Puni
library_note: It has a mirror like glossy pout. It is said that luster determines the ranking of the herd.

name: Gold Puni
library_note: Golden glowing Puni. It is said to bring good luck when seen.

name: Lavender Puni
library_note: This Puni has a tentacle that looks like lavender sprout on the top of its head. Its smell is so strong that adventurers don't like it.

name: Big Puni
library_note: They are not merged together, nor fat, they are just originally a plump species.

name: Shining Puni
library_note: This title is only given to those who have survived the grueling competition for survival. The Puni of all the Puni.

name: Rafflesia Puni
library_note: It has a way stronger smell than the Lavender Puni. If you are sensitive to smell, it will cause pain.

name: Darkness Puni
library_note: A huge species of Black Puni. It pops out of darkness like them, but stands out because of its presence.

name: Precious Puni
library_note: Giant Silver Puni. They often go out into the sunlight and boast their brilliance.

name: Giant Weasel
library_note: A common monster that inhabits any forest. It has strong family ties and always hangs out in herds.

name: Bluefin
library_note: A type of a Giant Weasel. He is so quick on his feet because of his timid nature.

name: Silky Fur
library_note: A type of a Giant Weasel. It produces a fine pelt but is very wary of humans.

name: Scarf Bunny
library_note: A type of the Giant Weasel. It is in search of a fitting scarf and sometimes leave their nests to travel.

name: Night Hunter
library_note: A type of a Giant Weasel. Because of the name someone gave it, it is often misunderstood and is actually not a good hunter.

name: Ruined Corrupter
library_note: A type of a Giant Weasel. It is especially violent compared to others within its species and requires vigilance.

name: Hide Stalker
library_note: This one is not just a Giant Weasel. It is capable of defeating monsters larger than itself.

name: Loppy Ear
library_note: A type of a Giant Weasel with large developed ears. Sensitively listens to sounds to avoid threats.

name: Mother Weasel
library_note: Recent research shows that there is a male Giant Weasel Mother, so scholars are thinking of renaming this one.

name: Savage Assassin
library_note: A type of a Giant Weasel that has grown to a huge size for some reason. It likes the way it looks now.

name: Hex Rabbit
library_note: A Giant Weasel transformed by magical power. Can both attack and heal itself with magic.

name: Large Antler
library_note: A monster with a large horn on the top of its head. It is said that the horn is also a sensory organ.

name: Holy Beast of the Stars
library_note: A subspecies of monster characterized by its large horns. It can sense when fellow monsters are in danger by using its horns.

name: Flower Pixie
library_note: A flower fairy awakened by sunlight. Fights to protect her favorite flower garden.

name: Illuminated Sylph
library_note: A flower fairy awakened by the moon. Naturally a night owl, so it always looks sleepy during the day.

name: Flower Gardener
library_note: A fairy who likes to take care of flowers. It fights using the magic powers from the flowers it grows.

name: Zephyr Pixie
library_note: According to one theory, is was formed from an exotic seed carried by the west wind that sprouted to become a fairy.

name: Eternal Guardian
library_note: A fairy that can live forever and watches over flowers and nature. It loves nature and shows no mercy to those who damage it.

name: Blazing Maiden
library_note: A fairy with a sad fate, burning its own flowers with a flame inside itself.

name: Hallowed Spirit
library_note: A fairy who gained sacred power through sunlight. Though it is holy, it is relentless.

name: Plumed Lorelei
library_note: A fairy who loves fruits. When the fruit it grows is taken away, it becomes furious.

name: Elder Fairy
library_note: A fairy who decided to devote its life to an old tree. But that ancient tree predeceased her.

name: Mirage Master
library_note: Mistaking the illusion created by magic for a flower, it continues to protect the flower, without even realizing it's an illusion.

name: Lunaria Angel
library_note: A hedonistic fairy born from the light of the moon. It enjoys life in the corner of a flower garden.

name: Nightmare Spirit
library_note: Born from a flower with the nature to deceive people. It shows people the dreams they don't want to watch.

name: Schwarzwraith
library_note: The reason sightings are so few is that its considered to be imaginary and gives everyone nightmares.

name: Sweet Nocturnal
library_note: A fairy in a black robe. It prefers dark places and is rarely ever seen in public.

name: Moon Veil
library_note: A fairy in a golden costume. They enchant those who see them by dancing gracefully.

name: Stone Golem
library_note: A monster born from the will of a Fairystone. The nature of the Fairystone it's born from determines its character.

name: Rock Puppet
library_note: A monster born from a block of ice charged with magical power. The ice so sharp, even more so than a knife.

name: Jewel Guard
library_note: A Fairystone monster that is devoted to refining its own body. It shines like a gemstone.

name: Fairystone Puppet
library_note: A monster that eats ore and gains its strength. Their territories are veins of ore where Fairystones can be extracted in abundance.

name: Metal Golem
library_note: A monster born from a lava-formed Fairystone. It has a violent temperament like this high temperature inside of it.

name: Meteorite Doll
library_note: A monster born from a meteorite. It contains a special ingredient that is not found anywhere else and its ecology is full of mystery.

name: Earth Master
library_note: It is said that the master was created a long time ago by mixing earth and soil with magic power. It is highly dangerous.

name: Rusty Onyx
library_note: An ore monster with rust colored lines. Its pattern changes depending on the impurities.

name: Colossus Golem
library_note: This ore monster became huge as a result of finding and collecting Fairystones.

name: Eternal Sculpture
library_note: A statue that was made by ancient people with Fairystones, which now has its own will. The creator is unknown.

name: Boulder Soldier
library_note: Artificially created stone soldiers. They have been following orders since they were created.

name: Darkomaton
library_note: Monsters that look like shadows with substance. It is said to appear before children who stay up late at night.

name: Noir Doll
library_note: The end of a soul with too many powerful unfulfilled desires. Wandering around as if driven by something.

name: Cramberry
library_note: A monster characterized by large red fruits. It is said to share its fruit with whoever it likes.

name: Harvest Prayer
library_note: A monster that bears blue-purple fruits. Just as it looks, the fruits taste like blueberries, but it doesn't really share.

name: Horned Sheep
library_note: They are monsters, but can be used as livestock. Everything, including the horns and fur is harvestable and valuable.

name: Ashen Wool
library_note: When they see something moving or red, they rush towards it. A poke with their horns is enough to kill someone.

name: Fluffy Sheep
library_note: A famous monster known for its high-grade wool. Nobles and others in the capital farm it for bedding.

name: Dreamcatcher
library_note: An alert sheep-type of monster. If you can defeat it, your dreams will come.

name: Giant Sheep
library_note: The blood of this monster is thicker than that of a normal sheep. No more, no less.

name: Mindlurker
library_note: It looks scary, but legend has it that it sucks up painful nightmares and takes the pain from you.

name: Mad Beast
library_note: A monster that collects people's memories and turns them into power. Appears in front of those with strong feelings and challenges them to fight.

name: Scaled Armadillo
library_note: A monster covered with a hard outer shell. When threatened, it curls itself up into a ball to protect itself.

name: Intact Carapace
library_note: A monster that protects itself with a reddish outer shell. It is more alert than the normal species and very seamless in defending itself.

name: Tiny Devil
library_note: A round, fluffy little monster. Dangerous because they rush at you whilst running energetically.

name: Ash Demon
library_note: A light-pigmented but energetic little monster. Dangerous because it charges at people as soon as it sees them.

name: Hot Evil
library_note: A cute-looking little monster. Dangerous because it lunges as an expression of affection.

name: Blue Fiend
library_note: A mischievous little monster that is more agile than normal. Dangerous because they rush at you as if they want to play.

name: King Devil
library_note: A small monster that has grown huge with an abundance of magical power. It is also more playful, making it even more dangerous.

name: Storm Elemental
library_note: A crystalline body of magic power. If it is mistaken for a Fairystone and mined, it will go berserk.

name: Icy Crystal
library_note: A crystalline body of magical power tinted pale. If you try to harm it, it will fight back using magic.

name: Spirit of Nature
library_note: A crystalline body of magical power transformed by high concentrations of magic. Eliminates enemies using a powerful magic hidden within its body.

name: Scrambled Energy
library_note: A golden crystalline body of magical power. It is considered to be a legendary existence and rarely ever seen.

name: Disaster Core
library_note: A gigantic crystalline body that is said to have lived since the age of myth. It stands in adventurers' way with great magical power.

name: Earth Plant
library_note: A plant monster that can stand on its feet and move. Its appearance changes drastically depending on the environment.

name: Root Spreader
library_note: A plant monster that adapts to its environment and turns light blue. No one knows why it turns light blue.

name: Great Tree Messenger
library_note: A plant monster that is colored flame red. However it is not actually burning.

name: Great Mistread
library_note: A poisonous-colored plant monster. It is dangerous and said to not be approached if seen.

name: Yggdrasil
library_note: A plant monster that has overgrown due to excessive nutrition. They rampage with excess physical strength, bulldozing the area around it.

name: Rageness
library_note: An ape-like Philuscha which are from the Underworld. Faces fierce competition in the Underworld.

name: Ground Builder
library_note: An ape-like Philuscha that cuts through enemies with its sharp claws. More intelligent and cunning than the regular species.

name: Ruler of the Forest
library_note: An ape-like Philuscha that thrives in the Underworld. Its hardened body hair is a sign of survival.

name: Spark Riser
library_note: An ape-like Philuscha that has risen to the top of its group. Its claws can even slice a rock clean in half.

name: Hell Keeper
library_note: The reason sightings are so few is that its considered to be imaginary and gives everyone nightmares.

name: Giant Sloth
library_note: A few ape-like Philuscha that were able to monopolize food. It's even hated by its own kind.

name: Feral Crow
library_note: A bipedal lizard monster. Hunts down enemies in packs using coordination.

name: Smart Ripper
library_note: A raptor species that has been trained in harsh environments. Hunts more agile and cunningly.

name: Ferocious Hopper
library_note: A raptor species that lives in remote wilderness. Able to leap very high on its developed hind legs.

name: Fierce Hunter
library_note: A species of raptor. If you beat one, they will recognize you as their own. However, due to so many guarding each other, it is not easy.

name: Tyrant
library_note: A Raptor King that leads its group. A strong enemy that fights at the front to protect its friends.

name: Living Armor
library_note: Not sure whether it's a monster clad with armor, or the armor itself is the monster.

name: Ghost Armor
library_note: They often appear at ruins and whisper to adventurers to leave armor behind.

name: Honor Guard Armor
library_note: The official armor of a prosperous country in ancient times. Able to manipulate swordsmanship at will, reflected by the user.

name: Gladiator
library_note: The armor of a warrior who lost his life in a duel. It should be dispersed gracefully, but was captured by magic and resurrected.

name: Legendary Warrior
library_note: Monster armor left behind by a well-known warrior. Even now it is a monster, the swordsmanship remains unchanged.

name: Immortal Knight
library_note: Knight monster who was felled on the battlefield. Its noble soul lives on within its armor, even after death.

name: Royal Admiral
library_note: Said to have been used to direct troops in the old kingdom. Even if there is no king to protect, it will always fight.

name: Heavy Warrior Armor
library_note: Monster armor originally produced for festivals. It was imbued with magic and turned into a monster.

name: Noble Paladin
library_note: A form of armor used by nobility and turned into a monster. It has a desire to rise to the top of the world.

name: Great Guardian
library_note: A guardian monster with a legendary treasure sword and armor. Demonstrates masterful swordsmanship, which shows its performance.

name: Demonic Phantom
library_note: A knight who died without fulfilling his great mission and turned into a monster. The more unfulfilled desires, the stronger it gets.

name: Berserker Shadow
library_note: A monster in armor left behind by a mad warrior called The God of War. Even in death, it continues to yearn for battle.

name: Temple Warrior
library_note: A monster in glass armor. No one knows what is inside the armor.

name: Shattered Breaker
library_note: A monster wearing armor made from amethyst. A meticulous choice of material, but the interior is a mystery.

name: Stinger
library_note: A scorpion-type monster holding sturdy scissors. Once it clips its prey, it won't let go.

name: Sharpened Scissors
library_note: A variant of the Stinger, raised in harsh environments. It is more aggressive and belligerent.

name: Pile Bunker
library_note: A Stinger variant. It has an even harder shell to repel attacks than the normal species.

name: Parching Demon
library_note: It is the highest rank amongst scorpion-type monsters. Their physical strength and intelligence are unmatched compared to the normal species.

name: Sleipnir
library_note: These are exceptionally intelligent scorpion-shaped monsters that can lead other monsters.

name: Dark Scout
library_note: A rat-type monster. It has effective night vision and can target its prey even in the dark.

name: Spine Rat
library_note: A strange looking monster with a hard dorsal fin. It dexterously uses its fin to hunt.

name: Ogre Head
library_note: A rat type monster with sharp horns. Not only its horns, but its scales grow like spines when threatened.

name: Shadow Vanguard
library_note: A relatively mild-mannered rat-type monster. Strongly territorial and hunts in packs.

name: Thrust Hedge
library_note: Utilizing its dorsal fins, this monster excels at underground activities. It will attack you from your blind spot to finish you off.

name: Shadow Eater
library_note: A rat-type monster that excels at stealth. Sneaks up on prey undetected.

name: Legion Needle
library_note: A rat-type monster with sharp needles. The needles can also fire off, useful for both offense and defense.

name: Mini Wyvern
library_note: A species of wyrm. Highly agile due to its small size and can move around in the air to taunt enemies.

name: Zephyr Feather
library_note: A species of wyrm. They are said to have the ability to read the wind and swoop in on the enemy.

name: Evil Orchis
library_note: A wyrm with sharp claws. A blow from its wings can even tear apart metal.

name: Stout Drake
library_note: A pterosaur monster, fat from its overeating. A masterful hunter of prey.

name: Mach Hawk
library_note: A species of wyrm. Their flight speed is said to exceed the speed of sound, but no one has ever seen them fly that fast.

name: Watcher
library_note: A species of wyrm. It is said to have very good eyesight and can detect enemies from far away and prepare for attacks.

name: Draconic Lord
library_note: A species of wyrm with leadership abilities more astonishing than even its own strength. Communicates with other species in an unknown way.

name: Giant Maw
library_note: A species of wyrm. Unlike Stout Drakes, its large figure is all muscles.

name: Mega Wyvern
library_note: A mutated mini wyvern that has grown to a gigantic size. Sometimes accompanied by protospecies as henchmen.

name: King of Storms
library_note: A type of wyrm that suddenly grew huge. Vindictive and doesn't let its prey escape.

name: Cloud Liner
library_note: A pterosaur with an unusually developed sense of smell. Can even detect prey that is out of sight.

name: Landbound Dragon
library_note: It is said that a spirit was bound to the land and took the form of a powerful wyrm to dissipate its unfulfilled desires.

name: Cursed Wing
library_note: Shadow dragon rarely appear in places where war took place. It is said that if you see them, misfortune will befall you.

name: Armored Wing
library_note: A species of wyrm with a steel-colored shell. No ordinary weapon can wound it.

name: Steel Raptor
library_note: A species of wyrm that has developed a greenish-blue color over the years. Its rusted yet unfading shell repels attacks.

name: Sprinting Bird
library_note: A species called a runner with strong legs. Good at running, but not so good at flying.

name: Massive Beak
library_note: A species of roadrunner with a huge beak. A blow from its beak, which gains momentum by running at a fast pace, is frightening.

name: Albatross
library_note: A species of running bird with feathers sold at a high price. However, they are too fast to be caught easily.

name: Wild Crest
library_note: A dark running bird species. The feathers have a beautiful cluster when processed and are therefore valued as ornaments.

name: Overwhelming Bird
library_note: A running bird that loves to run all hours of the day and night. They are also noisy and annoying.

name: Twilight Songbird
library_note: A running bird that runs around in the darkness of night. Has a unique ecology that feeds on human memories.

name: Lifeless Shadow
library_note: A reincarnated form of the Twilight Songbird after death. Its power increases with number of memories consumed during its life.

name: Twilight Assassin
library_note: A Philuscha with distinctive giddy eyes. Extends its long tongue to eat and attack.

name: Cloak-in-dagger
library_note: A Philuscha with a thorny shell. Can be deadly if it hits a body blow.

name: Shadow Assassin
library_note: A Philuscha with a voracious appetite. Swallows trees and even pieces of rock without concern.

name: Cipher Code
library_note: A strong Philuscha that has won the fight for food. Even the Oren struggle with its quick tongue attacks.

name: Hell Keeper
library_note: The giggling Philuscha, who has grown to a large size. Slow in movement, but quick with its tongue.

name: Slashblader
library_note: An agile wolf-like monster. Highly intelligent and utilizes armaments left behind by humans.

name: Spellblade Wielder
library_note: A wolf-like monster that is more fluffy than the normal species. Their pelts fetch a high price on the market.

name: Crimson Arms
library_note: A wolf-like monster with a reddish discoloration. The discoloration is caused by the magic power in the armor it wears.

name: Demon Slayer Wolf
library_note: A monster wearing a powerful magical tool created in ancient times. Shining as silver as the moon.

name: Sleipnir
library_note: A wolf-like monster that has fought many battles in the past. The attacks from its developed body are strong.

name: Hide Shark
library_note: This one has a shark-like appearance but can move on land. People are still investigating as to why it looks like this.

name: Megamouth
library_note: A shark-like monster. It has a well developed jaw that can even chip rocks.

name: Spinal Fin
library_note: A shark-like monster. Its hardened dorsal fin contains a unique composition and is treated as a new-type of mineral.

name: Grand Tusk
library_note: A shark-like monster. They dig holes to make their nests and their territory is full of pits.

name: Sandstorm Tyrant
library_note: A ferocious shark-like monster known as a tyrant. It seizes its prey and drags it straight to the ground.

name: Desert Lagoon
library_note: A shark-like monster often found in sandy areas. Can swim through the desert like an ocean.

name: Mind Ravager
library_note: A shark-like monster that devours memories. Particularly likes emotions such as anger and irritation.

name: Land Crawler
library_note: A blue fish-like monster that has evolved by an insatiable desire to reach land. Advances on its well-developed paws.

name: Soul Cleaver
library_note: A former sea creature that has adapted to land and has fought many generations of battles. With their well-trained fins, they can even fight land-based enemies.

name: Dark General
library_note: A powerful species of Philuscha that bears the name of a general. Its power comes from the Fairystone on its back.

name: Cluster Beetle
library_note: A species of Philuscha. It wields two well-developed horns and runs wild.

name: Shadow Commander
library_note: A stronger species of Philuscha that leads monsters in the Underworld. Rarely appears on the frontlines, but is very vicious.

name: Horned Demon
library_note: The strongest of the Philuscha. Not even a band of warriors from the Oren Tribe could take it down.

name: Rhino Fiend
library_note: Although small for its size, it has a strong body and is not often attacked due to its rampant behavior.

name: Old Castle Dragon
library_note: A gigantic flying dragon that makes its home in old ruins and abandoned buildings. They have a variety of attacks such as fireballs and tornadoes.

name: Dragon Lord
library_note: Originally a gentle dragon that watched over people but lost itself due to evil power.

name: Dragon of Light
library_note: A mysterious dragon whose dwelling and ecology are shrouded in mystery. Worshipped as a god in some regions.

name: Ravaging Queen
library_note: Reigning Queen of the Philuscha. Undermines and destroys everything.

name: Queen of Shadows
library_note: A jet-black queen whose entire body is cursed. Originally just a mere puppet.

name: Crownless Queen
library_note: A gigantic monster, much like the queen of the Philuscha. People fear her as much as calamity itself.

name: Floating Skeleton
library_note: A gigantic skeleton that floats in the air and moves autonomously. Both arms of steel require the utmost caution.

name: Skeleton Emperor
library_note: An enhanced species of Floating Skeleton. A special alloy provides additional hardness as well as flexibility.

name: Automaton
library_note: A giant soldier that appear to have been artificially created. The magic power that pervades its entire body emits light.

name: Sentry Guard
library_note: A high-level version of the Automaton. It shines with the color of brass. Mobility increased by detaching some of its armor.

name: Elder Treant
library_note: A giant plant-like life form lying deep in the forest. It has the power to change the entire environment around it.

name: Ancient Dragon
library_note: A giant life form that has been transformed by stealing the life force of its surroundings. Its open petals deceive humans and siphon off their power.

name: Deranged King
library_note: A giant King of the Philuscha species and lives deep in caves. Even its already robust shell becomes even more robust.

name: Gatekeeper
library_note: An artificial weapon for protecting ruins, powered by the Seeds of Light. What is its biological appearance a reference to?

name: Code of the Universe
library_note: A self-supporting defense weapon that lies in the deepest part of the Code of the Universe. Its mechanism cannot be unraveled by modern technology.

name: Orig. Code of the Universe
library_note: A forgotten weapon found at the top of the central tower on Rosca Island.
